<TITLE> 4 new VCs appointed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 24(bdnews24.com)  Four new vice-chancellors have been appointed to public universities, the education ministry said Tuesday. Besides, three pro-vice-chancellors and two treasurers have also been appointed. Md Raisuddin, deputy secretary at the education ministry, told bdnews24.com Dr Abu Yusuf Alam of Chittagong University will be vice chancellor of that university. Abdus Sobhan, professor of applied physics and electrical engineering department of Rajshahi University, will helm that university. Sharif Enamul Kabir, professor of the chemistry department of Rajshahi University, has been made vice chancellor of Jahangirnagar University, while professor Salauddin Ahmed of Shahjalal University of Science and Technology has been appointed vice chancellor. Professor M Alauddin has been made pro-vice-chancellor of Chittagong University, Md Nurullah pro-VC of Rajshahi University and Farhad Hossain of the statistics department pro-VC of Jahangirnagar University. Besides, Prof Shawkat Jahangir and Prof Abdur Rahman have been made treasurers of Jagannath and Rajshahi universities respectively. bdne
